	   <a name=10280079761001></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10280079761001><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>Damn you Verant.</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=177838><span id=Scholar>Senbik</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>45 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jul 30th 1:46 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey guys.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've been hearing a lot of SKs talking about how hard it is to get into raid groups 'cause we have no 'class defining' skill.  Since they nerfed Disease Cloud we 'supposedly' can be out-taunted by a paladin unless we use most of our mana supply.  Its really frustrating to hear all these people complaining about no raid invites and such when I'm still starting out... Makes me want to go make a cleric or something, heh.  Can anyone give some info on what a usual raid is like for an average SK?  Would be cool to see everyone's opinion and not just the whiners, thanks!<br>&nbsp;<br>Senbik -- Gnomish Shadow Knight of Bertoxxulous.<br>Vindayan -- Dark Elven Shadow Knight of Innoruuk.</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
